3337,541,'client_sound_title','Will Lopez-Founder of AdvisorFi'),(3338,541,'_client_sound_title','field_59242cf833e78'),(3339,541,'client_sound_content','“I believe that Toobler provided me the highest level of communication &amp; coding during my product development. The world has greatly benefited from hands of their innovative team!”'),(3340,541,'_client_sound_content','field_59242db433e79'),(3341,541,'project_flow_title','Challenge'),(3342,541,'_project_flow_title','field_59242dd533e7a'),(3343,541,'project_flow_content','One of the major challenges we faced was with the integration of Advisorfi with Xero accounting software. Xero has a very secure OAuth API, which is double encrypted, with two separate sets of keys at different stages in the request procedure. Our team had previous experience dealing with OAuth API integrations, but still making API calls to Xero proved to be more difficult than we anticipated.\r\n\r\nVery soon we realized the previous knowledge we had with writing OAuth API clients is not going to be good enough. We also couldn\'t find any account of writing Xero Partner API client using Node.js online. We got in touch with the API integration specialist at Xero, who confirmed that it was the first time anyone was trying to connect to the Xero Partner API using Node.js. So we decided to write our own node module for connecting to the Xero API. We took an existing OAuth client, tore it apart and added the extra parts that were needed for it to handle requirements specific to Xero API, such as handling double encryption, refreshing expired tokens, sending custom header parameter as Xero required etc. In the end, with the client\'s permission, we shared the implementation details of the API client we created with the Xero developer relations team to help them help other developers in the future.'),(3344,541,'_project_flow_content','field_59242df233e7b'),(3345,541,'project_flow_title2','Results'),(3346,541,'_project_flow_title2','field_59242e1733e7